      "side": 1,
      "message": "I put this here because I only wanted the msvc-posix-compat library pull in the srcs if we were doing a msvc build, not mingw. \n\nContents of msvc-posix-compat/CMakeLists.txt:\n\nset(msvc-posix-compat_windows_msvc_src\n        src/msvc-posix.c\n        src/getopt.c\n        src/gettimeofday.c)\nandroid_add_library(msvc-posix-compat)\nandroid_target_include_directories(msvc-posix-compat windows_msvc PUBLIC include/)\n\nSo it will only include the files for windows_msvc build. I can also just check the tag myself in the CMakeLists.txt and remove this change. What do you think?",
